  "footnotes": [
    "Mazandaran and the Caspian coast maintained semi-independent dynasties (Bavandid, Dabuyid, Maraashi) throughout the medieval period, even under nominal Caliphate suzerainty",
    "Khorasan was historically larger than modern Iranian Khorasan, encompassing parts of modern Afghanistan and Turkmenistan; it was the cultural heartland of Persian civilization under the Samanids",
    "The Ilkhanate (1256–1335) was the Mongol successor state covering most of Iran; its collapse triggered the fragmentation into Injuid, Muzaffarid, Jalayirid, and other regional dynasties",
    "The 1828 Treaty of Turkmenchay ceded the Caucasus (including most of Iranian Azerbaijan) to the Russian Empire; the remaining Iranian Azerbaijan is the column shown here",
    "The Mahabad Republic and Azerbaijan People's Government (1945–46) were Soviet-backed separatist states that collapsed after Soviet withdrawal"
  ]
